|WKO=====================================================================
|YKOUnique weapons and armour are one of a kind: only a single copy of
each can exist in the game at a time. While one is out in the world -
or in someone's hands - no second copy will appear. Uniques come from
their usual places in the world; mighty foes guard many of them.

A unique does not last forever. Roughly five days after it appears it
dissolves into the aether, and a wielded or worn unique pulsates
softly about half an hour before the end. Heed the warning.

The first player to pick up, wield, or wear a unique after a reboot
claims it. Claims are announced on the events channel and recorded
forever in the unique leaderboards. Claimed status clears at reboot,
so every boot is a fresh race.

|WKBCommands:|YKO
  |YKBuniques           |YKOList known uniques and whether each is claimed
                    this reboot or still available.
  |YKBuniques weapon    |YKOOnly weapons; |YKBuniques armour|YKO for armour.
  |YKBuniques claimed   |YKOOnly claimed; |YKBuniques available|YKO for the
                    unclaimed.
  |YKBuniques favorites [count]        |YKOMost-claimed uniques ever.
  |YKBuniques hoarders [count]         |YKOPlayers with the most claims.
  |YKBuniques playerfavorites [count]  |YKOEach player's most-claimed
                    unique. Counts run 1-50 and default to 10.

Just after a reboot the catalog rebuilds itself, so entries may keep
appearing for a few minutes while the refresh completes.

